DataElement.preferredDefinition: A non-proprietary, third generation modelling language. The Unified Modeling Language is an open method used to specify, visualise, construct and document the artifacts of an object-oriented software-intensive system under development. The UML represents a compilation of "best engineering practices" which have proven successful in modelling large, complex systems.:A grouping of things based on shared common attributes.:A description of the affiliation between two occurrences of Object Classes.:A registry item for which administrative information is recorded in an Administration Record.:Data about data; information that describes another set of data._An object fixed as a goal or point of examination; something to point at; a destination.:A grouping of things based on shared common attributes.:An elevated level or position or degree; greater than normal in degree or intensity or amount.:The number of elements in a set._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is an Integer (32-bit two's complement).
